fr/home/|title = QuantumSpecs team website|date = |accessdate = |website = |last = |first = }}</ref> group, director of joint team QuEST between the laboratories LPEM-ESPCI<ref name=\":0\" /> and INSP-UPMC,<ref>{{Cite web|title = Spectroscopy ov Novel Quantum States team at the Institut des NanoSciences de Paris|url = http://www.insp.upmc.fr/-Spectroscopie-des-nouveaux-etats-.html|website = www.insp.upmc.fr|accessdate = }}</ref> and member of direction board of LPEM.<ref name=\":0\" />\n\nThe research of Dimitri Roditchev at [[Moscow State University]] concerned studies of electronic properties of disordered [[metals]] and [[insulator (electricity)|insulator]]s, in relation with [[Metal\u2013insulator transition|metal-insulator]] and [[Superconductor Insulator Transition|superconductor-insulator]] [[phase transitions]]. In France since 1991, his activities include basic research<ref>{{Cite web|url = http://qs.lpem.espci.fr/home/research/basic-research/|title = QuantumSpecs basic research|date = |accessdate = |website = |last = |first = }}</ref> (ultimately confined superconductivity, quantum vortex, proximity phenomena in hybrid systems, near-critical superconducting states, superconductivity of atomic layers at surfaces in relation with spin-orbit interaction, metal-insulator transition etc.<ref>{{Cite web|url = http://qs.lpem.espci.fr/accueil/publications/|title = List of relevant publications|date = |accessdate = |website = |last = |first = }}</ref>) and engineering of high precision cryogenic equipment for scientific research.<ref>{{Cite web|url = http://qs.lpem.espci.fr/home/research/equipment-and-development/|title = Equipment and development|date = |accessdate = |website = |last = |first = }}</ref>\n\nThe teaching activity of Dimitri Roditchev includes lectures in Condensed Matter Physics (both basic and advanced levels), advising personal research projects at l[[ESPCI ParisTech|\u2019ESPCI-ParisTech]]. He is author of popular science articles and books,<ref>{{Cite web|url = http://www.cnrs.fr/paris-michel-ange/IMG/pdf/350.pdf|title = C. Noguera et D. Roditchev, \" Les multiples fronti\u00e8res du nanomonde \", Pour la Science, no 350, 2006, p. 122|date = |accessdate = |website = |last = |first = }}</ref><ref>{{Cite book|title = D. Roditchev, Microscopies en champ proche, in|last = |first = |publisher = Odile Jacob, Paris|year = 2002|isbn = 9782738111654|location = Paris|pages = 256}}</ref> public conferences<ref>{{Cite web|url = https://www.canal-u.tv/video/upmc/rencontre_autour_de_la_physique_a_la_decouverte_de_la_supraconductivite.8671|title = D. Roditchev \" Rencontre autour de l physique : A la d\u00e9couverte de la supraconductivit\u00e9 \" (2011), dans la s\u00e9rie \" Sciences \u00e0 c\u0153ur \" Universit\u00e9 Pierre et Marie Curie Paris 6.|date = |accessdate = |website = |last = |first = }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url = http://www.arts-et-metiers.net/musee/supraconductivite-ou-lart-de-faire-passer-le-courant|title =  Supraconductivit\u00e9 ou l'art de faire passer le courant ! Rencontres au Caf\u00e9 de techniques, (2011) CNAM Paris |date = |accessdate = |website = |last = |first = }}</ref> and interviews with the media.<ref>{{Cite web|url = http://www.rfi.fr/emission/20120625-1-infiniment-petit-peut-il-etre-visible/|title =  L'infiniment petit peut-il \u00eatre visible ? - RFI |date = |accessdate = |website = |last = |first = }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url = http://www.cnrs.fr/supra2011/spip.php?article15|title =  SUPRA 2011 - A \u00e9couter |date = |accessdate = |website = |last = |first = }}</ref>\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n== Selected bibliography==\n*{{Cite journal|title = Remarkable effects of disorder on superconductivity of single atomic layers of lead on silicon|journal = Nature Physics|date = June 2014|issn = 1745-2473|pages = 444\u2013450|volume = 10|issue = 6|doi = 10.1038/nphys2937|first = C.|last = Brun|first2 = T.|last2 = Cren|first3 = V.|last3 = Cherkez|first4 = F.|last4 = Debontridder|firs